	<tr align="left" valign="top">
		<td width="17%" nowrap class="BoardColumn">Author</td>
		<td width="83%" colspan=2 class="BoardColumn">
		<a name="62932832" width="85%">Topic:</a> 
		Proposed ruleset for a new EQ PvP server		
	</tr>
	
	<tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/anarion777?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">anarion777</a>&nbsp;<br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/anarion777"><font size="1">collection (0)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/anarion777"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 34<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Apr 03<br></span><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;1/20/04 5:31am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> Proposed ruleset for a new EQ PvP server</td></tr><tr valign=top><td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">In December I purchased Everquest Evolution and started playing EQ again for the first time in more than two years because Sony created the Discord promotional server. After the disaster of Shadowbane, I realize that Everquest PvP is the most fun I've ever had in an online game. Unfortunately, with Discord gone, I'm left with four very stale PvP servers to play on. <br>  <br> Discord was great because it was something new and it had a creative concept. Also, the limmited lifespan of the server made it so that PvP was the primary focus, as it should be on a PvP server. Thus, I'd like to submit for your comment the proposed ruleset for what I'll call the Guild War Server. I've tried to keep to an absolute minimum the amount of special coding that would be involved in bringing up this server, to give the idea a better chance of catching on with Sony. <br>  <br> Guild War Server <br>  <br> The Guild War Server is a team-based PvP server with an emphasis on guild competition. The server will be set up similar to Discord in that it will include only Everquest Classic and the Legacy of Ykesha expansion. The server will also have a scoring system similar to that of Discord, but on a guild rather than individual basis. No scores will be kept for individual players, just agregate scores for guilds. The server will have a lifespan of six (6) months, after which team and guild winners will be declared and the server taken down and wiped. <br>  <br> There will be no permadeath or item/coin loot on the Guild War Server. Instead, in PvP the victorious player or group will take from a vanquished opponent an amount of exp similar to what the group or individual would have gained for killing a MOB of the same level. Binding is only allowed in cities for all classes, and there will be a massive death affect which will last 20 minutes after a PvP death. This affect will lower all stats and make mana and hit point recovery extremely slow, thus reducing bind rushing.  <br>  <br> The storyline of the server is that it exists in a parallel world where none of the areas of the non-active expansions have been discovered, and Norrath is divided into a group of nine city-state alliances. The teams will be hard coded so that grouping, guilding and buffing will not be allowed outside your team. Starting cities with at least eight available classes will be a team unto themselves. Other teams will consist of an alliance of two starting cities. <br>  <br> 1. Halas/Sufefall Glade <br>  <br> In this parallel world of Norrath, half elves have been driven out of the lands of both humans and pure elves. Surefall Glade has become their home, and they have made alliance with the barbarians of Halas against the self-righteous humans of Qeynos. Available classes: 6. <br>  <br> 2. Neriak <br>  <br> In this parallel world, the troll race has been virtually wiped out. Although a few troll NPCs remain in the world, troll will not be available as a playable race. This is because even without trolls, the Neriak team is likely still the most attractive team in the game, given the proximity of Solusek A and B, and Najena. Available classes: 8. <br>  <br> 3. Kaladim/Rivervale <br>  <br> The short folk of Kaladim and Rivervale have made alliance against the other distrusted races. Available classes: 6. <br>  <br> 4. Paineel/Oggok <br>  <br> The minions of Cazic Thule have banded together in a natural alliance to spread darkness and destruction across Norrath. Available classes: 6. <br>  <br> 5. Erudin/Gukta <br>  <br> For mutual protection against the hated Ogres and corrupt Erudites, the denizens of Erudin and Gukta have banded together. Available classes: 7. <br>  <br> 6. Ak'Anon <br>  <br> In this world, the gnomes of Ak'Anon have disdained alliance and vowed to make Faydwer their own. The alignment of this city-state leans toward evil, and thus paladin will not be an available class. Available classes: 8. <br>  <br> 7. Qeynos <br>  <br> In this alternate world of Norrath, Freeport is wholely given over to the side of darkness, while all of the &quot;good&quot; humans have banded together in Qeynos. Their goodness, however, is of an arrogant and xenophobic brand. No evil classes can start here, and all half elves have been driven out. Available classes: 9. <br>  <br> 8. Freeport <br>  <br> The glorious Temple of Marr in North Freeport lies abandoned and defaced as the forces of darkness have completely taken over the city. Finding no tranquility in this corrupted city, the monk guild has also closed its doors. Available classes: 9. <br>  <br> 9. Kelethin/Felwithe <br>  <br> In times of darkness and war, even the elves have turned bitter and distrustful. Only pure elves are allowed citizenship in this city-state, and all of the half elves have been driven out. Available classes: 10. <br>  <br> The breakdown of available classes for the teams is as follows: <br>  <br> 1. Halas/Surefall: BST DRU RNG ROG SHM WAR <br> 2. Neriak: CLE ENC MAG NEC ROG SHD WAR WIZ <br> 3. Kaladim/Rivervale: CLE DRU RNG ROG PAL WAR <br> 4. Paineel/Oggok: BST CLE NEC SHD SHM WAR <br> 5. Erudin/Gukta: CLE ENC MAG PAL SHM WAR WIZ <br> 6. Ak'Anon: CLE ENC MAG NEC ROG SHD WAR WIZ <br> 7. Qeynos: BRD CLE ENC MAG MNK ROG PAL WAR WIZ <br> 8. Freeport: BRD CLE ENC MAG NEC ROG SHD WAR WIZ <br> 9. Kelethin/Felwithe: BRD CLE DRU ENC MAG RNG ROG PAL WAR WIZ <br>  <br> Each team has its advantages and disadvantages. Where some teams have an advantage in available classes, other teams have a geographical advantage with multiple bases of operation. For the PvP level range, I'm proposing an intermediate step between the +/- 4 or 8 of Rallos, Tallon and Vallon and the open PvP of Sullon. Starting at level 6, a player will be PvP+ to characters 5 levels higher. Every 5 levels, the plus range will increase by one. Thus, at level 11, a player is PvP+ to players 6 levels higher, +7 at 16, +8 at 21, etc.... The breakdown of level ranges is as follows: <br>  <br> Level/Range <br> 1-5. PvP- <br> 6. 6-11 <br> 7. 6-12 <br> 8. 6-13 <br> 9. 6-14 <br> 10. 6-15 <br> 11. 6-17 <br> 12. 7-18 <br> 13. 8-19 <br> 14. 9-20 <br> 15. 10-21 <br> 16. 11-23 <br> 17. 11-24 <br> 18. 12-25 <br> 19. 13-26 <br> 20. 14-27 <br> 21. 15-29 <br> 22. 16-30 <br> 23. 16-31 <br> 24. 17-32 <br> 25. 18-33 <br> 26. 19-35 <br> 27. 20-36 <br> 28. 21-37 <br> 29. 21-38 <br> 30. 22-39 <br> 31. 23-41 <br> 32. 24-42 <br> 33. 25-43 <br> 34. 26-44 <br> 35. 26-45 <br> 36. 27-47 <br> 37. 28-48 <br> 38. 29-49 <br> 39. 30-50 <br> 40. 31-50 <br> 41. 31-50 <br> 42. 32-50 <br> 43. 33-50 <br> 44. 34-50 <br> 45. 35-50 <br> 46. 36-50 <br> 47. 36-50 <br> 48. 37-50 <br> 49. 38-50 <br> 50. 39-50 <br>  <br> The graduated PvP range is designed to slowly make PvP more open as a player progresses in level without subjecting low level players to pointless attacks by high levels. In order to minimize immortal healing and buffing, and reduce power leveling, players will only be able to cast benneficial spells on teammates within their PvP level range. <br>  <br> Guilds will be limmited to 20 players in size, and players will be distributed evenly among the starting cities through a lottery system tied to guild registration. To play on the server, a player must go through the normal guild creation process to pre-register a guild for the server. The guild leader of each registering guild will then submit a preference list of starting cities for the guild, ranking the cities from most to least preferred. When pre-registration is completed, a lottery will be held to determine starting cities and order of guild creation. <br>  <br> For example, if 100 guilds pre-registered, then the lottery would assign a number 1-100 to each guild, with 1 being the first guild created. As guilds are created, one guild must be assigned to each starting city before a second guild can be created in that starting city. The guild with the lottery number 1 would be assigned to the top starting city on its preference list. If Guild 1 and Guild 2 had Neriak as their top preferred starting city, Guild 1 would start in Neriak and Guild 2 would start in its second choice. <br>  <br> To take the example a step further, let's say the top 10 guilds in the lottery happened to have the starting cities ranked exactly the same on their preference list. The list, ranked from most preferred to least, would look like this: <br>  <br> 1. Neriak <br> 2. Ak'Anon <br> 3. Qeynos <br> 4. Erudin/Gukta <br> 5. Kelethin/Felwithe <br> 6. Freeport <br> 7. Paineel/Oggok <br> 8. Kaladim/Rivervale <br> 9. Halas/Surefall <br>  <br> In this case, Guild 1 would start in Neriak, and Guild 2 would start in Ak'Anon, since a second guild cannot be created in Neriak until a guild has been created in all 9 starting cities. Thus, Guilds 3-9 would also be assigned to the corresponding city(s) on the preference list. Guild 10 would start in Neriak, its first choice, since one of each of the first 9 guilds was assigned to one of the nine teams. <br>  <br> I welcome your comments, and I would appreciate if you could forward a link to this thread to as many people as possible, especially current PvP players in EQ. If we can build a consensus on a ruleset for a new PvP server, we have a better chance of getting Sony interested in the idea. Post your comments here or forward them to buddy at riseup dot net. <br> <p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/Help/Faqs.aspx#lockedtopic">Locked Topic</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=62932832" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=795487">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=795487">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/renxerox?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">renxerox</a>&nbsp;<a href="/Help/Faqs.aspx#stars"><img align=absmiddle src=/images/star4.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="2,909 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/renxerox"><font size="1">collection (0)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/renxerox"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 2,909<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Dec 00<br></span><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;1/20/04 8:25am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 