 if they could make this the rule on all the pvp servers.  An additional rule I would like to see added would be more coding of high end weapons to make them unequippable by low levels (I've only played on Rallos for a few months, and I don't know how many deleveled epic rogues with Wrapped Entropy Serpent Spines I've been attacked by).  Also, certain spell effects that have too much utility in pvp, and are also good for griefing, should be reevaluated for effect and/or duration, such as blind, root, and snare.  The purpose of that would not be to make the server more blue, but to induce some level of parity between the teams.  It doesn't mean much for a team to have a sufficient number of starting classes if most of the classes that they have are not very good at low and mid-level pvp (like warriors, rogues, clerics and paladins).  Otherwise the server will be composed of nothing but druids, mages, shamans, wizards, shadow knights and necros running around ganking people who are trying to play the other classes, and there won't be many of those since the server is gonna be wiped, and few people will want to invest the time in developing a character for anything but short term pvp fun. <br> <p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/Help/Faqs.aspx#lockedtopic">Locked Topic</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=62998833" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=885358">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=885358">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/renxerox?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">renxerox</a>&nbsp;<a href="/Help/Faqs.aspx#stars"><img align=absmiddle src=/images/star4.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="2,909 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH &